modules.description: The module provides functions to print formatted representations of lists, arrays, hashtables, and tuples containing primitive values like strings, integers, floats, and characters. It supports nested collections (e.g., lists of tuples, arrays of primitives) and configurable formatting options such as prefix labels and float precision, using semicolons and delimiters to structure output. These tools are particularly useful for debugging, logging, or visualizing complex data structures with consistent, human-readable formatting.
